Title: ACT II


== DAY 01 — ARRIVAL


EXT. HOUSE ENTRANCE - MORNING


The camera is outside, wide.


A large house sits behind a metal gate. A car drives off frame, revealing all five characters.


NORITH
(to himself)
Okay.


AMRA with a bag on one shoulder and her camera bag on the other. She looks like she didn't sleep. Without thinking
about it she lifts her camera and photographs the
gate.


MONY looks around like he's checking for an exit.


VICHARA's already calm. She looks at the house the way she'd look at a business deal she hasn't agreed to yet.


VIVOTH looks at the house.


The camera holds on his face for a second too long.


It's not the face of someone seeing something for
the first time.


CUT TO:


INT. HOUSE MAIN HALLWAY - DAY


The camera follows them from behind as a STAFF
MEMBER walks them through.


Old tiled floors. A long hallway. Framed photos
on the walls, some black and white, some in color
but old. Big windows with light coming through.
Flowers in a vase that somebody arranged carefully.


Everything in this house looks like it was put
there on purpose.


AMRA slows down near one of the photos on the wall.


The camera moves to show what she sees.


A framed photo of two boys and two girls playing and laughing in a garden. The glass on the frame has a crack in it cutting between one boy and the other three.


She leans in to look closer.


STAFF MEMBER
This way please.


She keeps walking. But the camera catches her
taking a second glance.


CUT TO:


INT. HOUSE GUEST ROOMS - DAY


Quick cuts between five different rooms. (to subtly show each character's personality)


NORITH throws himself onto the bed. Bounces once.
Gives it a nod of approval.


MONY picks up a book someone left on the desk.
Flips through it. Puts it down.


AMRA sets her camera bag on the dresser very
carefully. Opens the window. Looks out at the
garden below.


VICHARA notices a framed photo sitting on the
bedside table. It is face down.


The camera is close on her hand as she picks it up
and turns it over.


It is a photo of a family having dinner. Old and
a little blurry. You cannot make out the faces
clearly. But the table, the room, the light coming
through the windows.


It is this house.


She sets it back facing up. Looks at it for a
moment.


Then goes to unpack her bag.


VIVOTH stands at a door frame, looking into a bedroom, ordinary, unimpressed, as if he's been there before.


CUT TO:


INT. HOUSE UPPER HALLWAY - DAY


The camera is at the end of the hallway watching
them come out of their rooms.


They all come out at almost the same time. Nobody
planned it. They just finished and ended up in
the same place.


They look at each other.


NORITH
So do we just stand here?


MONY
I think we wait.


NORITH
Wait for what?


MONY
For someone to tell us what to do.


NORITH
That is the most Mony thing you have ever said.


MONY
What, We have known each other for eighteen hours.


NORITH (mockingly)
And...?


AMRA almost smiles. It surprises her a little.
VIVOTH smiles slightly.
VICHARA is already walking toward the stairs.


VICHARA (mid walk)
There is a sitting room downstairs.


Everyone makes their way down.


CUT TO:


INT. HOUSE SITTING ROOM - DAY


The camera does a slow pan across the room as
they settle in.


A chess set on the table mid-game. Books on the
shelf. A small wooden carving on the shelf near the window. Old photos in frames. A room that has been lived in for a long time by someone who keeps things.


A STAFF MEMBER appears, puts down a tray of tea
and leaves without a word.


NORITH
Hey, so are you guys gonna explain why we're here?


The butler doesn't answer.
NORITH picks up a small bronze decoration from
the side table. Turns it over in his hands.


NORITH
This thing definitely costs more than my car.


MONY
That is not a high bar.


NORITH
See, this is why nobody likes you.


AMRA laughs. It surprises her a little again.


MONY almost smiles.


The camera finds VICHARA across the room. She is
holding the small wooden carving from the shelf.
She turns it over.


CLOSE UP on the base of the carving.


Two initials carved into the wood. V.S.


She sets it back. Her face doesn't change but she
remembers it.


VIVOTH sits a little apart from the group. Not
that he's unfriendly. Just comfortable on his own. He is
looking at the room the same way VICHARA is.
Taking it in slowly.


NORITH
Does anyone actually know anything about this man?


MONY
He is wealthy.


NORITH
Shocking.


MONY
He owns a painting worth more than we will earn
in our lives. So either very old family money or—


VICHARA
Or he made it himself.


NORITH looks around the room.


NORITH
Nobody makes this. You inherit this.


A quiet moment.


BUTLER
Dinner is ready. He's waiting for you.


Everyone proceeds to the dining room.


CUT TO:


INT. HOUSE DINING ROOM - NIGHT


WIDE SHOT.


The camera looks down the long table. THE MAN
sits at the far end. He is already there when they
arrive. Waiting but not in a hurry about it.


This is the first time they have really seen him
up close. He is old. His hands move slowly. But his
eyes move around the table quietly as they sit down,
taking everyone in.


The staff serve. Silence.


THE MAN
How are you guys settling in?


VICHARA
Pretty good, thanks for the hospitality.


THE MAN
Please, enjoy the food.


NORITH
It's really good.


THE MAN
The cook's been with me fifteen years now.


NORITH
Fifteen years. Now that's loyalty.


Small laughs from the table.
AMRA looks around the dining room. More framed photos
on the walls. More faces she cannot quite make out
from where she's sitting.


AMRA
Have you always lived here?


THE MAN
Ever since I came back.


AMRA
Alone?


A short pause.


THE MAN
Mostly.


Everyone goes back to eating. A moment of silence.


THE MAN
Tell me a little bit about yourselves.


A pause, as everyone waits to see who will go first.


AMRA
Well, I like photography...I was inspired after I found my dad's old camera.


THE MAN
That's nice, my brother also loved photography.


AMRA
My dad too.(exicted at first then her tone dropped) at least used to...


THE MAN (laughing)
My brother loved low shutter photography. I never understood it. Everything is smeared.


AMRA seems surprised by that comment. But shows no further reaction. MONY proceeds to say something.


NORITH (cutting MONY off & mid chew)
Wait, so the ones in the hallway, they're all smeared. Were those his photos?


MONY (to himself, staring at NORITH)
Wtf bro.


The question lands. A silent beat. As if no one wants to answer. A sensitive topic maybe.


THE MAN (avoidant, then confrontational)
Yeah, those are his. Also young man, you shouldn't speak mid chew, it's disgusting.


Everyone laughs.
NORITH glares at him. How rude.


NORITH (done chewing, frustrated)
Also, why tf are we here again?!


Everyone turns to THE MAN. Waiting for an explanation.


THE MAN (frustrated)
I'll get to that.


MONY glances at AMRA.
VICHARA glances at NORITH.
VIVOTH smiling slightly to himself.


VICHARA
I need to use the restroom.


VIVOTH (without missing a beat)
It's out that door, to the left.


VICHARA looks at him, slightly confused, but doesn't question it further. She moves out of her seat.


CUT TO:
INT. HOUSE CORRIDOR - NIGHT


WIDE SHOT


VICHARA closes the door behind her.
She proceeds down the hallway, skipping the restroom. It's quiet. She walks slowly, carefully observing the photos on the walls. Smeared like he said. Uncomfortable.


The scene builds tension. It gets eerie, as sounds become claustrophobic. She's looking at a particular photo. As she walks off, the camera stays on it, pushing in on the corner, initials...V.S.


CUT BACK TO:


INT. HOUSE DINING ROOM - NIGHT


CLOSE UP SHOT


NORITH (pushing)
So...I'm waiting?!


Everyone looks at the man.
The camera pushes in on him.


THE MAN
Well if you insist. You have two activities to complete this weekend.


NORITH looks confused, as if he's not satisfied with the answer. Everyone else is looking intently.


MONY
And what are these "activities" exactly?


THE MAN
You'll see by tomorrow.


Nothing else said.
But the table feels different now.


The camera switches to a high angle, like a fly on the wall, then to VICHARA in the hallway. She walks up to an old door, locked on the outside, eerie, as if its not supposed to be opened. Music builds suspense and mystery. As we zoom in to the lock on the door, music crashes.


CUT TO BLACK.


== DAY 02 — MORNING


INT. MONY'S ROOM - EARLY MORNING


The camera shows a clock on the wall, 4:07 AM. MONY's bags are packed. He is thinking. A close up on his face.

He moves to the hallway with his bags. Looking towards the end, then towards AMRA's room. The camera switches to his face, contemplating. Cymbals rise, almost uncomfortable.


CUT TO:


INT. HOUSE HALLWAY - MORNING (AFTER BREAKFAST)


The camera comes in from outside the doorway. Everyone is walking towards the painting room. The feeling is completely different energy from last night.


NORITH is already yapping.


AMRA has her holding her camera up taking pictures of the paintings. MONY is correcting something NORITH said. NORITH is not listening.


NORITH
I am telling you the fish made eye contact with me.


MONY
It was already filleted.


NORITH
Then explain the feeling.


AMRA
I believe you.


NORITH points at her.


NORITH
Thank you. Finally.


MONY
That is not the support it sounds like.


NORITH
(pointing at Mony)
This is why—


MONY
Nobody likes me. I get it.


Everyone laughs. VIVOTH smiles at VICHARA.


She sits back down without making anything of it.


FOLLOW TO:


INT. HOUSE PAINTING ROOM - DAY


WIDE SHOT


Big room. High ceiling.
Morning light comes in.


Five blank canvases on stands. Paint already set
out.


THE OLD MAN is already painting at his own canvas. Slow and calm.
Like this is just what mornings are.


The group walks in and stops.


THE MAN
Morning, how was breakfast? Y'all ready to paint?


NORITH
(low to Mony)
We're painting now?


MONY
Looks like so.


NORITH
I can't paint.


MONY
Well, unlike you, I can.


THE MAN
(looking towards NORITH)
Neither could most people who became painters.


Everyone picks a canvas and sits. NORITH picks up a brush like he is not sure what to do with it.


The room settles. Brush sounds. A comfortable kind of quiet.


AMRA starts badly. A stroke of blue that goes
nowhere. Then another. Then she stops thinking
about it and her hand starts moving differently.


NORITH's canvas is bad bad.


MONY leans over to look.


VICHARA (observing VIVOTH)
You paint well.


VIVOTH
Thanks.


VICHARA
Do you think he painted the one at the museum himself?


VIVOTH
I don't know. Probably.


VICHARA
Do you know what the painting was about?


VIVOTH (slightly dismissive tone)
How would I know. It was destroyed before I got a good look at it.


VICHARA
Why would someone destroy it? And why frame us?


NORITH (whispering loudly)
PROTESTORS!


VICHARA glares at him. MONY glares at NORITH.


MONY
What is that?


NORITH (confused thought Mony was asking about his painting, he looks down at his painting)
A window.


MONY (glancing over)
It looks like a square. Also where's the protestor?


NORITH
(one brow raised)
Art is subjective. Also there's no protestor. Are you high?

The camra pan to Vichara and Vivoth as they whip their heads to look at Norith as if they were trying to 
deflect the question back at him.

Mony just shakes his head defeated while Amra laughs softly.

The old man hand pauses as he takes in all this chaos and unhinge moment and smiles.
A smile that seem genuine and longing.

NORITH
(look at people around the room, Then nonchanlantly gets back to painting. one hand holding brush, 
other hand holding and shrugs)
What?

MONY
Unbelievable

MONY goes back to his own canvas. The camera looks at it.

It looks like a technical drawing.


AMRA walks past and glances at it.


AMRA
Did you label the sections?


MONY
(covering with his hand)
No.

NORITH( glancing over then let out a laugh)
Is this "I can paint" you were talking about?

MONY
precision, structure, and order are all important in art. But of course, your brain can't comprehend that. 

NORITH
Nerd

THE MAN peaks over at NORITH's canvas.

THE MAN
What's this?


NORITH
It's a window.


THE MAN (take a closer look at the canvas, try to look from different angles, then looks at Norith)


NORITH
(pause)
It's a brown window.


THE MAN (intrigued, trying to understand)
Abstract, I see. Where does it lead?


NORITH
It leads nowhere. It's a closed window.


THE MAN
Interesting...


NORITH (mockingly)
How about you, what are you painting?


THE MAN (showing his painting)
This...this is a Kintsugi painting. The golden seem crack like an old saying goes, "What was once broken....


MONY (casually finishing the sentences)
...may once again come together."


THE MAN (surprised and smile)
Exactly

CUT TO:

INT. HOUSE PAINTING ROOM - LATER

The group is cleaning brushes. 

The camera is on VICHARA cleaning her brush slowly.

She is looking at THE MAN's canvas on its stand.
She can see the bottom corner from where she stands.

A small signature.

P.S.

The camera cuts to the wooden carving on the shelf
from yesterday.

The V.S initials.

Then to the cracked photo frame in the hallway.

V.S. initials.

Back to VICHARA. She shakes her thought then look back up to see that Amara is staring at that same direction.
Amra is looking at the painting. Looking at the signature. Then look at each other for a moment.

THE MAN
Alright everyone, let's share what we all painted. 

Norith raised his hand up and was excited to share his painting.

MONY
I think we should start with Vichara.

The camera stays on Norith looking at Mony with a look of disbelieve. Mony act like he didn't notice that and looks at Vichara.

THE MAN
Vichara, what did you paint?

The camera locks onto VICHARA's painting, a locked door. It looks eerie, like a whole mystery is trapped behind the wooden door. the door is locked with a big golden lock. The lock is the only thing that looks new on the painting. the door is old, with a lot of cracks. The same door she tried to put her mind off the whole night but it kept coming back to her. The same door that has been haunting her since she got here.

VICHARA (She looks at the man before she reaveal her painting)

The man acts composed and calm, but there is a hint in his eyes betraying his thoughts. 

THE MAN (try to be non-chalant and shyte)
That is a very interesting painting, Vichara.

VICHARA (looking at the painting with a small smile)
Thank you. I think you know all to well about this door.

The room goes quiet. The camera closes in on everyone's face as the tension builds up

THE MAN
I do?

VICHARA
Yes, it's the door to one of your rooms. 

Everyone looks at the man.

THE MAN
Oh, that room (realising)...It's been locked for a long time now. One of my sibling used to stay there.

The camera zoom out to show the whole room. 
Seeing that everyone's unsettling gazes are all on him, he clears his throat.

THE MAN (pulling out a key from his pocket)
This is the key to that room. I guess you can go check it out if you're curious. 

Vichara's face shows a hint of surprise. 
She reluctantly holds out her palm. The man drops the key into her hand.

VIVOTH(looking at Vichara then the man)
So It's your sibling's room?? where are they now??

Vivoth's question caught everyone off guard. He doesn't talk much and nobody expected him to be that direct.

THE MAN
They... they have their own lives and their own families now. 

camera focus on vivoth's face. his expression is unreadable. but there is a hint of sadness in his eyes but his
lips curve up into a slight bitter smile.

VIVOTH
I see... So they abandoned you? Is that why you host this pathetic get together? ...with strangers?

The man's breath exelerates. He looks at Vivoth with a mix of sadness and confusion while maintaining his composure. Now they stare at each other like they are trying silently communicate through their eyes .

THE MAN (The man starts laughing out loud)

the camera pan to Norith who force an awkward laugh with him then stop when Vichara glares at him. Mony and Amara look at each other with a look of "what the f"

THE MAN (CONT'D)
(laughing) Me? Abandoned? No, no, no. You think anyone would be insane enough to abandon an old man with billions of dollars and estate like this? (laughing again) 

THE MAN(CONT'D)
(serious now) You're all here for my amusement. And you. Young man is either very funny or very stupid.

Vivoth looks so unfazed by the comment.

THE MAN(CONT'D)
Any more questions?

Amara raises her hand

AMRA
What's your name?

The man smiles. (Loki meme smile)

THE MAN
POSY

CUT TO:

INT. HOUSE KITCHEN - AFTERNOON - DAY

The group scatter around the kitchen. 
Vivoth washes his hands in the at the sink. 
Norith talks to Vichara. They take a glance or two at Vivoth in between sentences. 
Mony pour water into a glass and hand it to Amara. 

MONY
Why were we ushered into the kitchen? We were just having breakfast,no?

AMRA
I don't know. Let's just play along. We'll be able to go home soon.

MONY
Do you think...

before Mony can finish his sentence the staff open the door. They all move swiftly like shadow around the kitchen. Groceries, and ingredient in hand before lay it out on kitchen island. 

The Camera shift focus to Vichara and Norith that stop at at Norith face.
 
 NORITH
 Are they going to cook us? (his hands wrap around his neck) This is how every cannibal movie started? 

 VICHARA
 Norith! Calm down.

 Norith paces back and forth

 NORITH
 This is exactly like that one movie.  

Vichara look at Norith like he's loosing his mind.

NORITH (CONT'D)
 Vichara! Rich people are very sick and twisted. What if he has a rare disease and he want to brew us into some kind potion

VICHARA
Norith! I think you watch too much body horror film

The camera move to the man's assistant walk in with a mysterious box.

THE ASSISTANT
You may pick out a piece of paper from the box

NORITH
See! He has us pick a paper that going to determine what part of the meal we're going to be

Norith said as he shakes Vichara vigorously. 

NORITH(CONT'D)
You gonna become an appetizer and I gonna become a dessert.

He then move to stand in front of the assistant and begs

NORITH(CONT'D)
Sir...My body is full of fat. He wouldn't like it. Cook Vivoth. He got the leanest meat


Vichara slides her her hand into the box and pull out a paper. She open it and read

VICHARA
Dessert

NORITH
Believe me now??

The Assistant took the paper from Vichara's hand.

THE ASSISTANT
Miss Vichara. You'll be working at the dessert station. The man wants to share his recipe with you all. He figure instead of having you all bored from the wait. He's planning a cooking activity together.

MONY
Doesn't he have chef and a wave staff at his service?

THE ASSISTANT (CONT'D)
He enjoys cooking with people. Says it tells you a lot about a person.

MONY
(under his breath)
More than a background check?

Everyone picks their paper. Papers unfold. Roles are read.

NORITH(reading his paper)
"Main cook."

Silence.

MONY
(reading his, then looking at the assistant)
Cook prep.

He looks over at Norith. Then back at the assistant.

MONY (CONT'D)
So the old man is just going to starve us. That's the second activity. Starvation.

NORITH
Excuse me

MONY
Norith is going to give us all food poisoning and this man is going to watch and call it amusement.

NORITH
I am a perfectly capable—

MONY
Name one thing you have cooked successfully.

A beat.

NORITH
Toast.

MONY
Did it burn?

NORITH
...Slightly.

Mony turns away. NORITH points at the back of his head.

NORITH
This man is a hater and I want it on record.

VICHARA
(reading her paper)
Dessert.

She looks at AMRA.

AMRA
(already reading hers)
Me too.

They share a small look. Something easy passes between them.

VIVOTH
(reading quietly)
Prep.

He folds the paper neatly and sets it down on the counter.

---

CUT TO:

INT. HOUSE KITCHEN — CONTINUOUS

WIDE SHOT.

The kitchen splits into its own little worlds.

VIVOTH stands at the chopping board, quiet and efficient. He rinses lemongrass under the cold tap, peels it back layer by layer, bruises it with the flat of the blade without being told to.

MONY opens a drawer. Closes it. Opens another. Pulls out a ruler.

The camera holds on the ruler for a beat.

He sets it beside the board and begins measuring his cuts of galangal. Even. Precise. Each slice lands with a soft, deliberate thwack.

VIVOTH glances at the ruler. Says nothing.

MONY(not looking up)
Consistency matters.

VIVOTH
In cooking?

MONY
In everything.

VIVOTH looks at him for a second. Then goes back to his lemongrass.

---

Across the kitchen, NORITH stands at the stove with the expression of a man defusing a bomb.

THE MAN sits nearby on a stool, not rushing, watching everyone move around his kitchen the way he watched them at the dining table. Taking account.

THE MAN
Have you made Somlor Machu Kroeung before?

NORITH
I have eaten it many times.

THE MAN
That is not what I asked.

NORITH
...No. But how hard can it be.

THE MAN(small smile)
My sister used to say that too.

A shift. Something in the word sister*lands differently in the room. The camera catches VIVOTH's hands slow for just a moment before resuming.

NORITH(genuinely curious now)
You have a sister?

THE MAN
Two. And a brother.

NORITH
The one who did the photography?

THE MAN
Yes. The youngest.

He picks up his cup of tea. Holds it.

THE MAN (CONT'D)
My sister,the older one, she was the cook. Not professionally. But she cooked the way some people pray. With her whole chest. She made this exact dish every rainy season without fail. Same pot. Same cracked wooden spoon she refused to throw away.

The camera drifts to AMRA across the kitchen. She is listening while her hands work the palm sugar into the sticky rice for the Num Ee. She doesn't look up but she is very still.

THE MAN (CONT'D)
Food always taste better whe people make it together 

AMRA (quietly)
My dad says something like that too but we always beg him to stay awy from the kitchen

THE MAN looks at her.

THE MAN
I'm sure he's a great man.

AMRA smiles. Small. A little complicated.

---

NORITH stirs the pot. Then stirs it again. Then stirs it a third time in the wrong direction.

MONY (from across the kitchen, not even looking)
You're going to break the emulsion.

NORITH
The what?

MONY
Stop stirring.

NORITH
How do you know what I'm doing?!

MONY
I can hear you doing it wrong.

NORITH looks at the camera crew as if to say: do you see this man? He points at MONY.

NORITH
You know what, one day one day something you predict about me is going to be completely incorrect, and I am going to make a whole celebration about it.

MONY(labeling a container)
I'll prepare my apology speech in advance.

THE MAN laughs. A real one. Not polished. It surprises even him a little.

---

VICHARA and AMRA work at the dessert station. Banana leaves are folded with a quiet focus. The Num Ee dough sits between them, soft and pale yellow.

VICHARA(rolling)
Have you cooked much?

AMRA
Only when my mom lets me near the kitchen. He's very protective of her stove.

VICHARA
Mine too.

A small beat. They are both just rolling and folding.

AMRA(not looking up)
P.S.

VICHARA
What?

AMRA
The initials on his painting. P.S. And the photo in the hallway V.S.

VICHARA's hands don't stop. But she is listening.

AMRA (CONT'D)
For some reasons, I can't stop thinking about these initial. You feel it to right.

Vichara nods her head.

They look at each other.

AMRA
What's Posy's bother name ?

Neither of them has an answer.

The camera holds on the two of them a beat longer than it needs to.

---

INT. HOUSE KITCHEN — LATER

The smells have taken over the room now. Kroeung paste warm in the oil. The sharp brightness of tamarind. Lemongrass releasing its long slow exhale into the broth.

NORITH tastes from the ladle. Makes a face that could mean anything.

THE MAN(watching)
Well?

NORITH
I think it's right?

THE MAN
You don't know?

NORITH
It tastes like it tastes like something I've eaten before. Which is good, right?

THE MAN gets up slowly from his stool. Moves to the stove. Takes the ladle from NORITH, tastes it himself.

A long pause.

THE MAN
It tastes like my sister's.

Everyone looks up.

THE MAN sets the ladle down. Stands there for a moment with his back to the room.

THE MAN (CONT'D)(to himself, almost)
Broken spoon and all.

He turns back around. His face is composed. But something moved behind it.

THE MAN (CONT'D)
Alright. Let's eat.

---

INT. HOUSE DINING ROOM — AFTERNOON

The table. But different from last night.

Looser. The Somlor Machu Kroeung sits in the center in the same pot. Steam coming off it. Bowls of rice. The Num Ee wrapped neatly in their banana leaf parcels at the end of the table.

Everyone sits. NORITH serves himself first out of pure instinct then looks around and puts one scoop back.

NORITH
For good luck

MONY
What luck

NORITH
Shhh. Eating.

The first spoonful. The table goes quiet in a different way than it did last night. Last night it was the silence of strangers watching each other. This is something else.

MONY(setting his spoon down slowly)
Norith.

NORITH
Don't say it.

MONY
This is...

NORITH
I know.

MONY
How.

NORITH
I genuinely do not know. Some things cannot be explained by science. Do you have your apology speech ready?

AMRA is laughing. VICHARA shakes her head but she is smiling ... a real one this time, unguarded.

VIVOTH looks down at his bowl. Something quiet crosses his face. Not quite nostalgia. Something older than that.

THE MAN watches all of them.

His hands around his bowl. That same longing smile from the painting room. But fuller now. Like a room that hasn't had light in it for a long time, and someone just opened the window.

THE MAN(soft)
My sister would have liked you all.

Nobody answers right away.

NORITH (quietly, genuinely)
I would have liked her cooking tips.

Small laughter around the table.

THE MAN nods. Just once.

The camera pulls slowly back from the table, wide, until all five of them and the old man are just figures gathered around a warm meal in a house that has been quiet for too long.

FADE TO:

---

INT. HOUSE HOUSE UPPER HALLWAY - LATE AFTERNOON

The camera follows a lock that is now being unlocked. There was beat before a hand reach out to remove the lock and push the door open.

INT. LOCKED ROOM — CONTINUOUS
WIDE SHOT.

The door swings inward slowly.
The room is dark. The curtains are drawn and have been for a long time. Dust moves in the strip of light that comes in from the hallway behind her.

Vichara steps in.

Her hand finds the wall. A switch. Light.
The camera takes the room in with her.
It is full of paintings.

Not hung. Not displayed. Stacked against every wall, some wrapped in cloth, some bare, canvases facing in and facing out. Dozens of them. Leaning on each other like things that were put here temporarily and then never moved again.
The group has scattered after the painting session.

This was a studio.

In the center of the far wall, larger than everything else, covered in a drop cloth. The same one she saw at the museum. She takes off the cloth reveal the same destroyed painting. 

she stares at it for a long while before she put the cloth back on.

Then she realized a red ink stain on the cloth.

CUT TO

INT. HOUSE READING ROOM - EVENING

Amara, Mony and Norith stumble across a small room. like a tiny library.

Small room. Books everywhere. A desk by the window
covered in papers and small things. The kind of
